    {
      "id": "candidate-program-rubric-note",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Promotion Rubric",
      "position": {
        "x": 1080,
        "y": 280
      },
      "width": 500,
      "height": 380,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Promotion Rubric\n\nA candidate family should not drive code until it has:\n\n1. explicit v1 membership\n2. explicit deferrals and boundary cuts\n3. minimal field and lifecycle contracts for each approved type\n4. typed-edge pressure called out where plain references are not enough\n5. substrate dependency notes\n6. a summary surface consumable from a parent graph\n7. at least one open question that could still change implementation\n\nThis keeps node-set expansion disciplined instead of decorative.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
